product.name: Nike G.T. Cut 3 EP
product.description: How can you separate your game when it's winning time? Start by lacing up in the G.T. Cut 3. Designed to help you create space for stepback jumpers and backdoor cuts, its sticky multi-court traction helps you stop in an instant and shift gears at will. And when you're making all those game-changing plays, the newly added, ultra-responsive ZoomX foam helps keep you fresh for all four quarters. With its extra-durable rubber outsole, this version gives you traction for outdoor courts.

product.name: Nike Air Force 1 '07 LV8
product.description: Comfortable, durable and timeless—it's number 1 for a reason. The classic '80s construction is paired with golf-inspired details for style that tracks whether you're on court or on the go.

product.name: Nike Air Max Plus
product.description: Let your attitude have the edge with flame-like caging that adds heat to the streets while airy mesh keeps you cool. The Air Max Plus gives you a tuned Nike Air experience that offers premium stability and unbelievable cushioning.

snkrs.desc: Step into the ISPA Link Axis, a continuation of our journey to push the needle of footwear design. "Every part can be recycled", says the ISPA team. "It represents progress over perfection—creating a product with a second life in mind". Guided by the principles of modularity and waste reduction, the design uses interlocking components, zero glue and as few materials as possible. This results in a new look and feel, too. One thing remains the same: Nike Air cushioning adds responsiveness and the perfect amount of bounce. When you've finished wearing these shoes, simply drop them off at a participating Nike store for recycling. It's a reminder of our promise: everlasting progress towards the forever shoe. Imagine what comes next.

Originally released in 1982 and nearly shelved forever, it was the people and community that kept the Air Force 1 alive and established the silhouette as the icon it is today. During its reign in the mid 1990s, the Air Force 1 was introduced in many lifestyle iterations that transcended the court and pierced through culture, such as the 1996 'Ivory Snake'.Last reissued in 2019, the cult-classic 'Ivory Snake' now returns in true form, complete with a leather upper, faux-snakeskin hits on the Swoosh and backtab, as well as true-to-OG Nike Air branding on the backtab.

Exploring the theme of duality through a Parisian lens, this edition of the Nike SB Dunk Low juxtaposes grunge and glam with a Baroque-inspired toile print. Evoking pastoral French streets and rococo aesthetics, the canvas upper reveals hidden Dragon Red suede underneath, the more you skate in them.The vibrant print and decorative gold accents showcase the dynamic relationships of beauty and brutalism with contrast stitching, ornate detailing, custom gold insole and a vintage-inspired Sail outsole. Evoking Paris' unique relationship with fashion, design and artistry, this Dunk reinterprets 17th and 18th-century aesthetics through a modern lens with skateboarding as a physical conduit for self-expression

The classic skate shoe that works on the board—and off. This premium take on the Dunk Low is crafted with velvety nubuck leather and a gum outsole, bringing a dash of allure every time you land a trick.

Premium materials. Stunning finishes. Cushioned comfort. This AF-1 makes a statement by adding the perfect polish to your outfit. With its throwback hoops style, we raised the stakes with Star Blue ostrich-textured leather, Metallic Gold graphics and a gum outsole. Tempted? Step into the '82 classic and carry your style into the future.

The Air Force 1 returns with a fresh mix of colours and materials. Crisp white leather is combined with durable textiles in the quarter panels and toe box for a breathable, flexible feel. Light British Tan trim brings a luxe look, while Photo Blue details on the midsole add a dab of colour to the classic design. The padded, low-cut collar is paired with Nike Air cushioning for plush comfort with every step. Step into the AF-1 and walk with legends.

The original Air Ship was the shoe MJ wore between his explosive potential and actualised greatness. It signified that his new dreams were taking shape. Continue the legend in this elegant edition. Sail leather is wrapped with Rust Pink overlays, while pops of Gamma Green on the insoles and tongue label add fresh energy to this soft palette. Vintage block lettering stitched on the collar and that classic midsole treatment drum up '84 throwback appeal.

Premium materials. Stunning finishes. Cushioned comfort. This AF-1 makes a statement by adding the perfect polish to your outfit. With its throwback hoops style, we raised the stakes with black ostrich-textured leather, Metallic Gold graphics and a gum outsole. Tempted? Step into the '82 classic and carry your style into the future.

The legendary design of the AJ11 redefined the look of basketball. This sleek, low-cut edition lets you redefine your off-court style with breezy textiles wrapped in smooth patent leather overlays. The full-length Air cushioning and tinted outsole soften your step, while the plush collar hugs your ankle for comfort. Wherever you take it, the AJ11 remains an unbeatable blend of elegance and attitude.

Inspired by the rogue, colour-clashing band of misfits from 2001, the Dunk Low 'Plum' returns. Taking its cues from the original, this re-release features an offbeat mix of Eggplant and Daybreak hues. And since looks aren't everything, we combined premium nubuck leather with that signature padded low-cut collar for an elevated feel. Staying true to its DNA, this oddly dressed Dunk is rooted in '80s hoops heritage, so you can rock 'em with a wink to the culture and a nod to the history.

Available 01/06 at 7:30 am The comfy classic is back. With a wide toe box and lateral lacing, the Air Footscape delivers an alternative fit for natural motion. The asymmetrical woven details pull double duty, punctuating the breezy textile and soft suede upper and adding another level of foot-hugging containment. Inside, you'll find a plush foam midsole and Nike Air cushioning in the heel for extra comfort. Step in and say, "ohhhhhh". By Gopika

Step into the ISPA Link Axis, a continuation of our journey to push the needle of footwear design. "Every part can be recycled", says a designer from the ISPA team. "It represents progress over perfection—creating a product with a second life in mind". Guided by the principles of modularity and waste reduction, the design uses interlocking components, as few materials as possible and zero glue. When you've finished wearing them, drop them off at a participating Nike store to help extend their life.

Available 06/06 at 9:30 am Comfortable, durable and timeless—the AF-1 is a fan favourite for a reason. Classic '80s construction paired with perforated leather brings style that tracks whether you're on the court or on the go. This special edition is decked out in black from top to bottom, plus a pop of Game Royal on the insoles for a little something extra.

Renowned designer Matthew M. Williams continues to coax fashion into new spaces. For this ambitious project, Nike and MMW drummed up a purposeful goal to create a performance running shoe. But instead of being built for the road, the Zoom 6 TRD Run x MMW was developed with treadmill runners in mind. To achieve this, the duo used key insights from runners to help inform the design. It uses the same full-length carbon-fibre plate and Air Zoom unit as the Alphafly Next% to give you a highly responsive feel underfoot. Plus, React foam is sculpted and stacked from heel to toe for a smooth yet durable ride. Taking inspiration from the Victory Elite track spike, the Flyknit upper provides breathability while maintaining the necessary support to help you stay with it. And since no one wants to get their laces snagged in the treadmill (or hit pause for adjustments), we updated the laces by adding notches to help prevent them from coming untied. It's got everything you need to go the distance.

After more than a decade, this mule is making a comeback in luscious Limestone suede. It blends a grippy outsole with a more cushioned midsole, bringing both comfort and traction while you're wandering off the beaten path or navigating the urban terrain. And thanks to its easy-to-wear design that can be dressed up or down, the ACG Rufus is sure to earn a spot in your footwear rotation. Go ahead—slip into pure bliss.

In '97, the Air Terra Humara was born for bold, brave wanderers. The trailblazers charging through the woods with destinations unknown. Serving the pioneers grinding to carve a new path for themselves in running and life, the rugged trail-running classic was the answer. Back for a victory lap on the streets, this lively edition of the Air Terra Humara brings a layered look thanks to Alchemy Pink suede, Diffused Blue woven textiles and University Gold accents. A lugged outsole and plush foam midsole come equipped with a Max Air unit in the heel, keeping you grounded in cushioned comfort.Today, the Air Terra Humara returns for a parade of adventure through the urban landscape. Whether you remember these shoes with a grin or regret never having got a pair, now's your chance to add them to your collection. The Humara is back—and extending a warm invitation.

What makes the perfect latte? Traditionally speaking, it's 1/3 espresso to 2/3 steamed milk. Different baristas may tell you different things—and some baristas guard their secrets. Lucky for you, we won't. We think the world's best latte is this AJ1 High. Smooth leather in a perfect blend of black and tan hues is combined with swirling insole graphics inspired by artisan milk patterns. This is the shoe that warms your soul on a cloudy morning.

In 2008, Lunar took its legendary bounce to the streets for the first time. Fast-forward 15 years and the plush foam midsole your feet fell in love with has been remastered and amplified for the city. Now equipped with breezy textiles and supportive cables in the upper, it delivers a lightweight, stable feel you'll want to wear season after season. And with a fresh, neutral colourway, this pair is sure to make a springy statement—wherever you roam.

kids.name: Tatum 2
kids.description: Pulled out of the vault, these low tops are back. Inspired by the original Wings logo and design of the AJ1, these all-day, everyday shoes are ready for whatever. Smooth leather uppers and a big embossed logo will help you stand out, however you style 'em.

kids.name: Jordan Nu Retro 1 Low
kids.description: An iconic look that lasts. This AJ1 pairs the classic design of the original with premium materials that will keep you going all day.

kids.name: Nike Blazer Low '77
kids.description: This iteration of the AJ1 re-imagines Mike's first signature model with a fresh mix of colours. Premium materials, soft cushioning and a padded ankle collar offer total support and celebrate the shoe that started it all.

kids.name: Air Jordan 1 Low
kids.description: Zion's third signature shoe celebrates the dedication he puts in to crafting his singular game. Packed with court-ready tech, it's designed for ballers who are masters of both land and air. Stay low and contained, then explode skywards, with a cushioned return to earth. The Zion 3 helps hold you down—so you can fly your own way.

kids.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid
kids.description: Pulled out of the vault, these low tops are back. Inspired by the original Wings logo and design of the AJ1, these all-day, everyday shoes are ready for whatever. Smooth leather uppers and a big embossed logo will help you stand out, however you style 'em.

kids.name: Zion 3
kids.description: Zion's third signature shoe celebrates the dedication he puts in to crafting his singular game. Packed with court-ready tech, it's designed for ballers who are masters of both land and air. Stay low and contained, then explode skywards, with a cushioned return to earth. The Zion 3 helps hold you down—so you can fly your own way.

kids.name: Nike Air Max Plus
kids.description: Who says kids don't deserve big cushioning? Not us. Get a taste of our legendary Tuned Air technology with the Nike Air Max Plus. From the school playground to your back garden, these comfy kicks are ready to play with breathable mesh fabric up top and a durable rubber sole underfoot. Plus, wavy design lines and iconic plastic accents celebrate bold style.

kids.name: Nike Blazer Mid '77
kids.description: Powered by flowers, these sneakers are all about stopping to appreciate the little things. A legend on the basketball court when first released in the '70s, the Nike Blazer Mid '77 is now an icon off the court with its mid-top collar and durable design. Throwback style with modern materials means you can run, skip and jump in comfort.

kids.name: Nike Dynamo 2 EasyOn
kids.description: Meet the shoes designed to keep up with your little one. Easy, snug and built for play at any time, the Nike Dynamo 2 EasyOn is all about helping kids get going fast. They can stomp down on the collapsible heel and slip their feet in. Or, if they're not quite ready to do it themselves, you can show them how it works by pushing down on the heel. Worm-like lines across the stretchy fabric upper wrap little feet in flexible comfort and support.

kids.name: Nike Flex Advance
kids.description: Pulled out of the vault, these low tops are back. Inspired by the original Wings logo and design of the AJ1, these all-day, everyday shoes are ready for whatever. Smooth leather uppers and a big embossed logo will help you stand out, however you style 'em.
kids.colors: Pink Glaze/Violet Ore/Light Violet Ore/Pink Glaze

kids.name: Nike Air Force 1 LV8 2
kids.description: Make a splash in shoes as fun as you. As cool today as when it first dropped more than 40 years ago, the AF-1 is a classic you can count on. Its durable construction, Air cushioning and grippy tread will see you through break time after break time. Pops of bright colours and reflective design Swoosh logos add eye-catching style. And while these sneakers look great fresh out of the box, they remain cool when covered in scuffs and scrapes. In fact, they might be even better.

kids.name: Nike Star Runner 4 NN SE
kids.description: Made for running to catch the ice-cream van, games of tag and races to the end of the street and back, this special-edition Nike Star Runner 4 lets you blast off into fun. Soft cushioning in the midsole helps provide a comfortable, springy return so every skip, hop and stride you take puts you one step closer to the finishing line. Plus, the tread grabs at pavement, grass and gravel to help give you extra grip. A rubber-wrapped toe box toughens up the construction so you can go further in the same pair of sneakers.

kids.name: Nike Sunray Protect 2
kids.description: The Nike Sunray Protect 2 Sandals deliver total toe coverage and outsole traction that's perfect for outdoor play. Hook-and-loop straps make on and off easy, while openings on the top of the shoe promote airflow when little feet get hot.

kids.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid SE
kids.description: Take note: the adults in your life might have rules, but they can also inspire some amazing drip. Inspired by the wallpaper in MJ's childhood home, this AJ1 rocks bold florals and colour-blocked canvas.

kids.name: Nike Jr. Phantom Luna 2 Academy
kids.description: You've found the net, whether you set up a pal with a great pass or made a fantastic move. Now, go and score. This boot has a sticky texture where you kick the ball the hardest. That way, you have control of your shot when the net is in range. We created it with goals in mind.

kids.name: Nike Air Max 90 LTR
kids.description: The Nike Air Max 90 takes the original look to a new level with more comfort and flexibility, while keeping the classic Max Air cushioning you know and love.

kids.name: LeBron XXI SE 'Movie Night'
kids.description: Where will your game take you? Lace up the latest from the King and find out. With Air Zoom units and soft cushioning, the LeBron XXI (also known as the LeBron 21) offers you flexibility and power without slowing you down with excess weight. Ideal for rim runs, fast breaks and racing up and down the court, they'll help you keep playing at the top of your game until the final buzzer sounds.

kids.name: JA 1
kids.description: Ja Morant became the superstar he is today by practising his game wherever possible. That same drive for greatness led to Ja seeing a childhood dream come true when he signed with Nike. On top of getting a signature shoe, he received a Nike employee badge, which is like an all-access pass to our World Headquarters. Full of lightweight and springy cushioning, this shoe celebrates Ja's love of the Swoosh and his rise from long-time brand admirer to signature ambassador.

kids.name: Nike E-Series 1.0
kids.description: Shoes made for almost any occasion. Playtime? Sure. School? Yes. Activities with friends? Of course! The Nike E-Series 1.0 is the everyday shoe. The highlight is a lace-free design that stretches wide (helped by a hidden strap) so it's easy to slip feet in. Combining plush comfort underfoot and stability where it's needed, we have 1 goal: making sure you're confident and have fun every time you pull on your kicks.

kids.name: Nike Team Hustle D 11
kids.description: From first steps to future first baskets, cover all of playtime with the Nike Team Hustle D 11. Our top priority with this edition of the Team Hustle D series was making them easy to get on. Big straps let you open the shoes up wide so little feet can slip in and get going. Plus, cushioning is more plush than previous editions, helping make each step more comfortable. The ultimate play shoe just got better.
kids.colors: Summit White/Coconut Milk/Light Photo Blue/Barely Volt
